The food here was so tasty and "raw" indeed! This was my FIRST time eating falafel and a veggie burger and NOT getting gassy at all due to them not using beans. The burger was so tasty and healthy (could've used a bit more meat, tomato sauce, and cashew nut "cheese") but was flavored like no other! Had this sweet smoky flavor.  The falafel could've fooled me! Would've loved a bit more of those little balls for the sad as well. I will most definitely be ordering from here again and thank this place for spurring me to start making my own at home "no bean or soy" falafel and vegan burgers at home. The delivery took a reasonable amount of time.  A suggestion would be to add some fresh hummus and pita bread or warm thick chip to the menu. And some sort of "fries" like sweet potato or something. These could be used as "sides" to the meals as they are a bit pricy for single items...  Highly recommended for vegetarians, vegans, raw foodists, and humans in general! :) 4/5
